cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper deals with automatic facial action coding using deep learning models, specifically variational autoencoders. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Gaussian Processes, which is a popular approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper focuses on the application of these models in human-computer interaction (cs.HC), which is another likely sub-category.
